sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Case is created in Microsoft Dynamics CRM.

Inputs:

  • Title - Title of the case.
  • Customer Type -Supported options are :
    • Account
    • Contact
  • Customer - Retrieves the records based on customer type selection.
  • Primary Contact - Retrieves the records of all the contacts.
  • Case Type - Retrieves the choice list of the field of case type.
  • Description - Description of the Case.
  • Is Escalated - Supported options are :
    • Yes
    • No
  • Priority - Retrieves the choice list of the field priority.
  • Email Address - Email Address of the field.
  • Additional Fields - Uses dynamic template to populate additional fields.

Outputs:

  • Case ID - ID of the Case.
  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • Provided value for Title input is invalid.
  • Provided Primary Contact is invalid and does not belong to the value provided in Customer input or the specified contact is already provided in the Customer input.
  • Provided value for Email Address input is invalid.
  • One or more inputs are invalid or not provided.
  • Provided value for Additional Fields is invalid as already provided.
  • Invalid username or password/token or the token has expired.
  • The user does not have sufficient permission to perform this action.

Additional Notes: Primary Contact can only be set if the Customer type is Account and if the Contact is already a part of the Account.

To use this action, the corresponding Microsoft Dynamics CRM connection and credential must be created and associated with the Microsoft Dynamics CRM Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Create Case
